<div class="page-header">
<h2>Ward // DTM -cp <small>v1.0.0
<br>by DoomRobotBoy</small>
</h2>
</div>
Ward is a DTM -cp map in which all the control points are conditional, meaning they serve a purpose and can thus help the team that is in control of them. Destroy 80% of the castle on the hill (the monument) to win. The monument can only be destroyed with TNT.<br><br>
<img src="http://i.imgur.com/mK484Pe.png" class="img-rounded"><br><br>
There are 5 control points on this map. 1 big one and 4 small ones. The big one in the center is necessary for your team to get TNT as killreward - if you don't have the hill you will not get tnt for every kill. The small control points give, if one controlled, the originally owning team a slowness effect of 2 seconds. So the control points next to the red castle give red a 2-sec slowness effect when the cp is controlled by blue. Capturing multiple of these control points doesn't do anything.<br>When spawning you will receive a defender's kit which we will be lost when you leave your own castle. The kit cannot be retrieved until death.
<br>You can only place oak wood planks below y=20.<br>TNT can be placed everywhere but does only do damage against players and the castles.<br>
The water is 2 blocks deep.<br><br>
